NOW SHE'LL FIND A WAY ♪

00:15.473 --> 00:17.142
{\an7}♪ WITH HELP FROM
HER BEST FRIENDS ♪

00:17.225 --> 00:19.436
{\an8}♪ THEY'LL SAVE THE DAY ♪

00:19.519 --> 00:20.937
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:21.020 --> 00:22.689
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:22.772 --> 00:26.443
{\an7}♪ TRUE TO HERSELF,
DOING WHAT'S RIGHT ♪

00:26.526 --> 00:27.902
{\an8}♪ HER HEART IS BRIGHT ♪

00:27.986 --> 00:30.780
{\an8}♪ SHE'S NELLA
THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

00:33.408 --> 00:34.784
TRINKET: OH, MY GOSH!

00:34.868 --> 00:36.953
I'M SO EXCITED.
I'M SO EXCITED.

00:37.036 --> 00:38.288
I KNOW, RIGHT?

00:38.371 --> 00:39.956
{\an1}I CAN'T BELIEVE IT'S
FINALLY TIME

00:40.039 --> 00:41.499
FOR CASTLEHAVEN ROLLERFEST!

00:41.583 --> 00:43.376
YOU'RE GONNA LOVE IT, TRINK.

00:43.460 --> 00:44.711
OH, I'M SURE.

00:44.794 --> 00:47.130
BUT ARE YOU SURE YOU
WANT ME TO BE

00:47.213 --> 00:49.132
YOUR PARTNER FOR
THE CONTEST?

00:49.215 --> 00:51.801
I'VE NEVER ACTUALLY
ROLLER-SKATED BEFORE.

00:51.885 --> 00:53.178
{\an8}YOU'LL BE FINE.

00:53.261 --> 00:56.055
{\an7}BESIDES, THERE'S NO ONE
I'D RATHER ROLLERFEST WITH

00:56.139 --> 00:56.639
{\an7}THAN YOU.

00:56.723 --> 00:58.975
I'LL DO MY BEST.

00:59.058 --> 01:00.685
I MEAN, I WAS BORN

01:00.769 --> 01:02.979
WITH LOTS OF NATURAL
UNICORN DANCINESS.

01:03.062 --> 01:04.647
♪ DA DA DA DA! ♪

01:04.730 --> 01:07.567
SO I JUST KNOW I'LL BE
SKATING IN NO TIME.

01:07.650 --> 01:10.487
{\an1}NELLA: COME ON.
LET'S GO WIN THIS CONTEST.

01:10.570 --> 01:12.781
{\an1}HELLO, SIR. I'D
LIKE SOME SKATES, PLEASE.

01:12.864 --> 01:14.324
♪ DA DA DA DA! ♪

01:14.407 --> 01:15.116
[APPLAUSE AND CHEERING
IN DISTANCE]

01:17.786 --> 01:19.913
TRINKET: WE'D BETTER GET
WARMED UP

01:19.996 --> 01:21.664
BEFORE I TRY
MY FIRST-EVER

01:21.748 --> 01:23.500
TRIPLE-FLIPPLE,
TUTTI-FRUTTI,

01:23.583 --> 01:24.876
BACKWARDS SALCHOW FLIP.

01:24.959 --> 01:28.046
THAT SOUNDS LIKE A PRETTY
COMPLICATED MOVE, TRINK.

01:28.129 --> 01:30.298
MAYBE WE SHOULD START SLOW.

01:30.381 --> 01:33.760
RIGHT. WARM UP FIRST,
TRIPLE-FLIPPLE SECOND.

01:33.843 --> 01:35.470
{\an1}UH, TRINKET, WE'RE GONNA
NEED ROLLERSKATES.

01:35.553 --> 01:37.847
I KNEW THAT.

01:37.931 --> 01:40.350
ROLLERSKATES FOR TWO COMING
RIGHT UP.

01:40.433 --> 01:42.727
{\an1}NOW, THERE'S JUST A FEW
THINGS TO REMEMBER, TRINK,

01:42.811 --> 01:43.895
{\an1}AND YOU'LL BE
UP AND SKATING IN NO TIME.

01:43.978 --> 01:46.397
LIKE WHEN TO SMILE AT
THE JUDGES

01:46.481 --> 01:47.982
OR HOW TO MAKE SURE
LIGHTS CATCH

01:48.066 --> 01:49.442
MY SPARKLY SADDLE?

01:49.526 --> 01:51.528
HEE HEE! NOT EXACTLY, TRINK.

01:51.611 --> 01:53.196
{\an1}MORE LIKE, WHEN YOU GET
OUT THERE, BE SURE

01:53.279 --> 01:59.160
{\an1}TO KEEP YOUR HOOVES STRAIGHT,
THEN STEP AND GLIDE.

01:59.244 --> 02:01.246
{\an1}UH, TRINK?

02:01.329 --> 02:03.581
STAND BACK, ROLLER FANS.

02:03.665 --> 02:06.376
THIS UNICORN IS READY
TO BUST A MOVE.

02:06.459 --> 02:09.378
{\an1}HOLD ON, TRINKET. LET'S
START SLOW, REMEMBER?

02:09.461 --> 02:13.132
SLOW? THERE'S NO TIME
FOR SLOW, NELLA. AAH!

02:13.216 --> 02:14.676
{\an8}OOH! ARE MY LEGS

02:14.759 --> 02:16.302
{\an8}SUPPOSED TO WOBBLE
LIKE THIS?

02:16.386 --> 02:18.930
{\an1}JUST KEEP YOUR HOOVES
STRAIGHT, TRINK.

02:19.013 --> 02:21.349
WHOA!

02:21.432 --> 02:23.226
THERE.
SEE? I'M FINE.

02:23.309 --> 02:26.688
{\an1}OK. NOW, JUST STEP
AND GLI--

02:26.771 --> 02:28.940
OH, NELLA, WHO NEEDS
THAT STUFF?

02:29.023 --> 02:30.900
I'LL JUST LET MY NATURAL
UNICORN DANCINESS

02:30.984 --> 02:32.485
DO ALL THE WORK.

02:32.569 --> 02:33.444
I'LL BE FI-I--

02:33.528 --> 02:34.696
TRINKET!

02:34.779 --> 02:38.908
[TRINKET SCREAMING]

02:38.992 --> 02:41.369
{\an1}HOLD ON, TRINK. WATCH OUT
FOR THOSE DOORS.

02:41.452 --> 02:42.579
WHAT DOORS?!

02:42.662 --> 02:47.000
OH, THOSE DOORS!

02:47.083 --> 02:48.710
{\an1}LOOK OUT!

02:47.083 --> 02:48.710
NELLA!

02:48.793 --> 02:51.546
{\an1}DON'T WORRY.
I'LL SAVE YOU, TRINK.

02:51.629 --> 02:53.381
MY HEART IS BRIGHT,

02:53.464 --> 02:55.258
TIME TO BE
A PRINCESS KNIGHT.

02:55.341 --> 02:57.302
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

02:57.385 --> 02:58.094
♪ IT'S TIME TO
SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

02:58.177 --> 03:01.139
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

03:01.222 --> 03:02.891
♪ MY COURAGE SHININ'
BRIGHT ♪

03:02.974 --> 03:05.143
♪ NOW I AM ♪

03:05.226 --> 03:06.102
♪ THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

03:06.185 --> 03:11.149
NOW, THAT'S A LOOK
I CAN ROLL WITH.

03:11.232 --> 03:12.400
AAH!

03:12.483 --> 03:14.569
HERE I COME, TRINK.

03:14.652 --> 03:18.448
UNICORN COMING THROUGH!

03:18.531 --> 03:21.659
TRINK, WAIT!

03:25.121 --> 03:30.460
P.U. NOW THIS
REALLY STINKS.

03:34.756 --> 03:38.509
WHOA! LOOK OUT!

03:38.593 --> 03:40.762
{\an1}WOMAN: COME AND GET
YOUR DELICIOUS...

03:40.845 --> 03:42.972
ICE-CREAM SUNDAES.

03:43.056 --> 03:44.307
TRINKET: WHOA!

03:44.390 --> 03:47.518
PLEASE FORM
AN ORDERLY LINE.

03:51.481 --> 03:52.815
{\an1}NELLA: UH!

03:52.899 --> 03:54.192
{\an1}GOTCHA.

03:54.275 --> 03:55.485
TRINKET? TRINKET?

03:55.568 --> 03:57.445
{\an1}[RUNNING
IN ROLLER-SKATES]

03:57.528 --> 04:00.657
ARE YOU OK?

03:57.528 --> 04:00.657
OHH...

04:00.740 --> 04:03.242
YEAH.

04:03.326 --> 04:05.745
{\an1}WHY DID I EVER THINK
I COULD SKATE?

04:05.828 --> 04:08.498
I'M A UNICORN.

04:08.581 --> 04:11.918
{\an1}WHO EVER HEARD OF
A ROLLER-SKATING UNICORN?

04:12.001 --> 04:14.879
TRINK, YOU'VE JUST
STARTED. YOU'LL LEARN.

04:14.963 --> 04:16.880
YOU JUST NEED TO
BELIEVE YOU CAN DO IT,

04:16.964 --> 04:18.966
AND YOU'LL GET YOUR
CONFIDENCE BACK.

04:19.050 --> 04:20.969
I DON'T THINK SO, NELLA.

04:21.052 --> 04:24.347
{\an1}NOTHING'S GOING TO HELP
THIS UNICORN SKATE.

04:24.430 --> 04:27.642
{\an1}I'M AFRAID YOU'RE GONNA
NEED TO FIND A NEW PARTNER

04:27.725 --> 04:30.186
FOR ROLLERFEST.

04:27.725 --> 04:30.186
BUT, TRINK--

04:30.269 --> 04:32.563
I'M SORRY, NELLA.

04:32.647 --> 04:35.066
AW.

04:35.149 --> 04:37.026
[SIGHS]

04:37.110 --> 04:38.528
HUH? OOH!

04:40.113 --> 04:42.198
SHINY.

04:42.281 --> 04:43.282
{\an1}[CHUCKLES]

04:43.366 --> 04:45.368
{\an1}THEY SURE ARE BEAUTS,
AREN'T THEY?

04:45.451 --> 04:47.161
FINEST SKATES I EVER MADE.

04:47.245 --> 04:49.872
THEY'RE SIMPLY MAGICAL.

04:49.956 --> 04:51.749
MAGICAL SKATES.

04:51.833 --> 04:53.876
JUST IMAGINE
WHAT I COULD DO

04:53.960 --> 04:55.878
WITH MAGICAL SKATES.

04:55.962 --> 04:57.046
UH, TRINKET?

04:57.130 --> 04:58.298
WE COULD WIN
THAT CONTEST.

04:58.381 --> 05:00.299
HUH?

04:58.381 --> 05:00.299
I'LL TAKE THEM.

05:00.383 --> 05:01.718
NO NEED
TO GIFT-WRAP.

05:01.801 --> 05:03.761
I'LL BE WEARING THEM
IN NO TIME.

05:03.845 --> 05:05.263
THEY'RE ALL YOURS.

05:05.346 --> 05:06.764
TRINK,
DO YOU THINK

05:06.848 --> 05:08.307
THESE SKATES
ARE MAGICAL?

05:08.391 --> 05:09.851
OF COURSE I DO.

05:09.934 --> 05:11.102
{\an1}AND NOW OUR PROBLEMS
ARE SOLVED,

05:11.185 --> 05:14.522
THANKS TO THESE
MAGICAL SKATES.

05:14.605 --> 05:16.024
OH, TRINK, I THINK
YOU MISUNDERSTOOD.

05:16.107 --> 05:18.484
THESE SKATES AREN'T
MAGI--

05:18.568 --> 05:20.528
{\an1}COME ON, NELLA.
WE GOT TO GET GOING.

05:20.611 --> 05:22.739
{\an1}WE'VE GOT A ROLLERFEST
CONTEST TO WIN.

05:22.822 --> 05:25.199
NO, TRINK, WAIT.

05:25.283 --> 05:27.201
OH, NO.

05:29.829 --> 05:31.372
THERE. I'M ALL SET TO DO

05:31.456 --> 05:32.832
SOME MAGICAL ROLLER-SKATING.

05:32.915 --> 05:36.169
BUT, TRINK, THAT'S WHAT
I'M TRYING TO TELL YOU.

05:36.252 --> 05:37.795
THOSE SKATES AREN'T--

05:37.879 --> 05:40.590
ARE EXACTLY WHAT I NEED
TO HELP ME SKATE.

05:40.673 --> 05:43.718
I'M REALLY SORRY
I LET YOU DOWN EARLIER.

05:43.801 --> 05:46.220
I JUST DIDN'T THINK
I COULD DO IT.

05:46.304 --> 05:47.889
I LOST MY CONFIDENCE.

05:47.972 --> 05:50.391
BUT WITH THESE,
I'M GOING TO SKATE

05:50.475 --> 05:53.102
LIKE, WELL, MAGIC.

05:53.186 --> 05:56.272
NOW, LET'S GO. WE'VE
GOT A CONTEST TO WIN.

05:56.355 --> 05:58.733
TRINK. OH, NO.

05:58.816 --> 06:00.735
TAKE IT SLOW.

05:58.816 --> 06:00.735
GOOD IDEA.

06:00.818 --> 06:02.945
I'M SURE
IT TAKES A SECOND

06:03.029 --> 06:04.781
FOR THE MAGIC
TO KICK IN.

06:04.864 --> 06:06.908
{\an1}TRINK,
THEY'RE NOT MAGIC.

06:06.991 --> 06:09.285
{\an1}JUST REMEMBER, KEEP
YOUR HOOVES STRAIGHT,

06:09.368 --> 06:11.287
THEN STEP AND GLIDE.

06:11.370 --> 06:14.290
GLIDE. OK!

06:14.373 --> 06:15.041
I CAN DO THIS.

06:15.124 --> 06:17.001
I'VE GOT MAGIC SKATES.

06:17.085 --> 06:21.297
STEP, STEP. GLIDE.

06:21.380 --> 06:22.965
TRINK, YOU'RE DOING IT.

06:23.049 --> 06:25.718
I TOLD YOU.
THESE MAGIC SKATES

06:25.802 --> 06:26.803
ARE WORKING
LIKE A CHARM--

06:26.886 --> 06:28.971
A MAGIC CHARM.

06:29.055 --> 06:31.933
IT'S NOT MAGIC, TRINKET.

06:32.016 --> 06:33.017
{\an1}THE MORE YOU SKATE, THE MORE
CONFIDENT YOU FEEL.

06:33.101 --> 06:35.853
[TRINKET CHUCKLING]

06:35.937 --> 06:38.314
DID SOMEONE CALL FOR
A SKATING UNICORN?

06:38.397 --> 06:41.818
SIR COACH: LET'S GET THOSE
TEETH GRINNING

06:41.901 --> 06:43.236
AND WHEELS SPINNING, FOLKS.

06:43.319 --> 06:46.197
IT'S CASTLEHAVEN ROLLERFEST!

06:46.280 --> 06:47.615
FAN: I LOVE
ROLLERFEST.

06:47.698 --> 06:52.078
{\an1}I'M SO GLAD WE GET TO BE
PARTNERS AFTER ALL, NELLA.

06:52.161 --> 06:54.664
ME, TOO, TRINK.

06:54.747 --> 06:59.585
ON YOUR MARKS.
GET SET. SKATE!

07:01.754 --> 07:04.841
{\an7}COME ON, SKATES.
THIS IS OUR MOMENT.

07:04.924 --> 07:07.552
{\an8}WOW. YOU'RE DOING
GREAT, TRINK.

07:07.635 --> 07:11.347
{\an7}I KNOW. SO LET'S
TRY GOING BACKWARDS.

07:11.430 --> 07:16.811
STEP, STEP, GLIDE
FROM SIDE TO SIDE,

07:16.894 --> 07:19.355
ALL IN MY STRIDE.

07:19.438 --> 07:20.606
WHOA.

07:20.690 --> 07:21.899
{\an7}OOH, I'VE GOT A GOOD FEELING
ABOUT THIS, TRINKET.

07:21.983 --> 07:24.318
{\an7}ME, TOO.

07:24.402 --> 07:25.486
{\an1}FAN: YAY!

07:25.570 --> 07:26.112
[MALE SKATERS CHUCKLING]

07:26.195 --> 07:29.365
FAN: OH, IMPRESSIVE.

07:29.448 --> 07:34.328
{\an1}COME ON, SKATES.
I'M COUNTING ON YOU.

07:34.412 --> 07:36.706
NELLA:
OOH. NICE MOVE.

07:36.789 --> 07:38.291
YOU, TOO, PARTNER.

07:38.374 --> 07:39.750
MALE SKATER: HUZZAH!

07:39.834 --> 07:41.210
[SKATER'S PARTNER CHUCKLING]

07:41.294 --> 07:44.463
SPECTATOR:
OOH, LOOK AT THEM!

07:44.547 --> 07:45.298
MM-HMM.

07:45.381 --> 07:48.885
{\an1}[GASPS]
WOW. DID YOU SEE THAT?

07:48.968 --> 07:51.387
YEAH. THAT
MOVE WAS SO COOL.

07:51.470 --> 07:53.306
WE'VE GOT TO TOP IT, NELLA.

07:53.389 --> 07:55.433
{\an1}TIME FOR THE TRIPLE-FLIPPLE,
TUTTI-FRUTTI,

07:55.516 --> 07:57.560
BACKWARDS SALCHOW FLIP.

07:57.643 --> 07:58.769
{\an8}ARE YOU SURE?

07:58.853 --> 07:59.854
{\an8}I DON'T THINK WE'RE
READY FOR THAT YET.

07:59.937 --> 08:04.567
{\an7}ABSOLUTELY. TIME TO WORK
YOUR MAGIC, SKATES.

08:04.650 --> 08:06.569
{\an8}COME ON, NELLA!

08:06.652 --> 08:08.946
{\an8}OK!

08:15.203 --> 08:16.662
WHOA! UH--

08:16.746 --> 08:19.332
{\an1}WHOO-HOO!

08:19.415 --> 08:20.291
WOW! OOH!

08:20.374 --> 08:22.126
TRINKET: LOOK OUT!

08:22.210 --> 08:23.920
WHEW.

08:24.003 --> 08:29.800
{\an1}OH, NO. MY MAGICAL SKATES,
THEY'RE--THEY'RE BROKEN!

08:33.679 --> 08:35.264
[SIGHS]

08:35.347 --> 08:37.933
{\an1}TRINK, I'VE GOT YOU
SOME SKATES.

08:38.017 --> 08:38.893
WE'VE GOT TO GET
BACK OUT THERE.

08:38.976 --> 08:42.104
I CAN'T SKATE WITH
THOSE, NELLA.

08:42.188 --> 08:44.690
THEY'RE NOT EVEN
MAGICAL.

08:44.774 --> 08:47.777
WITHOUT MY SPECIAL
SKATES, I'M HOPELESS.

08:47.860 --> 08:50.947
{\an1}BUT, TRINKET, YOUR SKATES
WEREN'T MAGICAL.

08:51.030 --> 08:54.575
TIME FOR THIS
UNICORN TO--WAIT.

08:54.659 --> 08:56.118
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

08:56.202 --> 08:58.079
{\an1}I'VE BEEN TRYING TO TELL
YOU ALL ALONG, TRINK.

08:58.162 --> 08:59.455
{\an1}YOU WEREN'T SKATING
BECAUSE OF MAGIC.

08:59.538 --> 09:02.625
WHAT? OF COURSE
I WAS, NELLA.

09:02.708 --> 09:04.877
HOW ELSE DO YOU
EXPLAIN MY MOVES?

09:04.961 --> 09:06.295
{\an1}YOU WERE JUST
FEELING CONFIDENT,

09:06.379 --> 09:07.880
NOT BECAUSE OF MAGIC

09:07.964 --> 09:10.132
{\an1}BUT BECAUSE YOU'VE BEEN
PRACTICING ALL DAY

09:10.216 --> 09:11.759
{\an1}AND GETTING BETTER
AND BETTER.

09:11.842 --> 09:14.512
SO OUT THERE
ON THE RINK,

09:14.595 --> 09:18.557
THAT WASN'T
MAGIC SKATES?

09:18.641 --> 09:19.725
NOPE. YOU WERE CONFIDENT.

09:19.809 --> 09:23.187
THEN WE'VE GOT TO GET
BACK OUT THERE, PARTNER.

09:23.271 --> 09:25.690
{\an1}YEAH. WE'VE GOT
A CONTEST TO WIN.

09:25.773 --> 09:30.152
{\an1}SIR COACH: AND LOOK WHO'S BACK
IN THE ROLLERFEST CONTEST.

09:30.236 --> 09:34.031
{\an1}IT'S PRINCESS NELLA AND HER
SKATING UNICORN--TRINKET.

09:34.115 --> 09:35.783
TRINKET:
HOOVES TOGETHER,

09:35.866 --> 09:38.452
AND STEP, STEP, GLIDE.

09:38.536 --> 09:39.787
YOU'VE GOT THIS,
TRINK.

09:39.870 --> 09:43.124
YEAH, I DO. I'M SKATING.

09:43.207 --> 09:49.964
IT'S LIKE MAGIC,
ONLY IT'S ALL ME!

09:50.047 --> 09:52.842
{\an1}NELLA AND TRINKET HAVE GOT
THEIR WORK CUT OUT FOR THEM.

09:52.925 --> 09:56.804
{\an1}THEIR COMPETITION
IS SKATING LIKE PROS.

09:56.887 --> 09:58.222
COME ON, NELLA.

09:58.306 --> 10:00.516
{\an1}WE'VE GOT TO SHOW THESE
JUDGES SOMETHING SPECIAL.

10:00.599 --> 10:02.810
YOU KNOW
WHAT THIS CALLS FOR?

10:02.893 --> 10:05.354
{\an1}YOU MEAN
THE TRIPLE-FLIPPLE,

10:05.438 --> 10:07.023
TUTTI-FRUTTI...

10:07.106 --> 10:08.858
BACKWARDS SALCHOW FLIP.

10:08.941 --> 10:09.692
ARE YOU SURE?

10:09.775 --> 10:12.194
{\an1}REMEMBER WHAT HAPPENED
LAST TIME?

10:12.278 --> 10:14.530
THAT WAS JUST BECAUSE
YOUR SKATE BROKE.

10:14.613 --> 10:15.448
WE CAN DO IT THIS TIME.

10:15.531 --> 10:17.325
WE JUST HAVE TO HAVE
THE CONFIDENCE.

10:17.408 --> 10:21.704
ALL RIGHT. IF YOU SAY SO.

10:21.787 --> 10:25.249
HERE WE GO!

10:29.003 --> 10:30.963
{\an1}WHOA!

10:29.003 --> 10:30.963
WHOA!

10:33.215 --> 10:34.717
{\an1}OOH!

10:33.215 --> 10:34.717
[GASP]

10:39.472 --> 10:42.224
SIR COACH:
OH! WHAT AN INCREDIBLE JUMP!

10:42.308 --> 10:46.312
AMAZING! UNBELIEVABLE!

10:46.395 --> 10:50.900
{\an1}AND THE WINNERS OF
THE CASTLEHAVEN ROLLERFEST,

10:50.983 --> 10:53.277
PRINCESS NELLA
AND TRINKET.

10:53.361 --> 10:56.238
{\an1}WOW.
WHAT FANCY SKATING.

10:56.322 --> 10:59.784
CAN YOU SHOW US
THAT MOVE?

10:59.867 --> 11:02.078
SURE. IT'S A PIECE OF CAKE.

11:02.161 --> 11:05.331
{\an1}IT JUST TAKES STYLE,
SKILL, AND...

11:05.414 --> 11:07.833
A LITTLE BIT OF
MAGIC?

11:07.917 --> 11:10.086
{\an1}HA HA! NO.

11:10.169 --> 11:12.505
JUST CONFIDENCE.

11:10.169 --> 11:12.505
AW.

11:12.588 --> 11:15.174
[CHEERING AND APPLAUSE]

11:20.679 --> 11:23.599
CAN'T WAIT! CAN'T WAIT!
CAN'T WAIT! CAN'T WAIT!

11:23.682 --> 11:25.226
NELLA: TRINK, WAIT UP.

11:25.309 --> 11:28.145
OOPS. SORRY, NELLA.
I JUST CAN'T WAIT.

11:28.229 --> 11:30.106
WE'RE GONNA BE STARS.

11:30.189 --> 11:32.441
I KNOW, RIGHT?

11:32.525 --> 11:33.359
{\an1}IT'LL BE SO MUCH FUN
TO BE IN A PLAY.

11:33.442 --> 11:35.194
AND TELL A REALLY
GOOD STORY,

11:35.277 --> 11:38.197
"THE BRAVE DRAGON."

11:38.280 --> 11:39.365
WAIT. WHAT'S THAT
ABOUT AGAIN?

11:39.448 --> 11:42.785
{\an1}IT'S THE TALE OF HOW
A BRAVE AND NOBLE DRAGON

11:42.868 --> 11:45.037
SAVED ALL THE CRITTERS
IN THE WOODS

11:45.121 --> 11:46.789
FROM AN EVIL WIZARD.

11:46.872 --> 11:48.082
THAT IS A REALLY
GOOD STORY.

11:48.165 --> 11:49.458
[LAUGHTER]

11:49.542 --> 11:52.628
BLAINE: ROAR! ROAR! ROAR!

11:52.711 --> 11:54.171
HI, SIR BLAINE.

11:54.255 --> 11:56.298
GARRETT:
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:56.382 --> 11:57.758
{\an1}PRACTICING MY AMAZING
DRAGON ROAR,

11:57.842 --> 12:02.054
BECAUSE I'M GONNA PLAY THE PART
OF THE BRAVE DRAGON, OF COURSE.

12:02.138 --> 12:03.806
OOH, THAT'S THE PART
I WANT, TOO.

12:03.889 --> 12:06.434
OH, NELLA, NELLA, NELLA.

12:06.517 --> 12:07.476
{\an1}YOU CAN'T BE
THE BRAVE DRAGON.

12:07.560 --> 12:11.397
TRINKET: AND WHY,
EXACTLY, NOT?

12:11.480 --> 12:12.481
{\an1}BECAUSE
IT'S THE BEST PART.

12:12.565 --> 12:15.985
{\an1}AND I'M THE BEST--
BEST ACTOR, BEST SINGER,

12:16.068 --> 12:20.823
BEST DANCER, BEST AT LISTING
ALL THE THINGS I'M BEST AT.

12:20.906 --> 12:22.366
HA HA! WE'LL SEE, BLAINE.

12:22.450 --> 12:24.243
{\an1}BUT WE DON'T KNOW
WHAT PART WE'LL GET YET.

12:24.326 --> 12:25.828
YEAH. SIR COACH
STILL HAS

12:25.911 --> 12:26.954
TO GIVE THEM OUT.

12:27.037 --> 12:27.955
I'M NOT WORRIED...

12:27.037 --> 12:27.955
HUP! HUP...

12:28.038 --> 12:31.292
SIR COACH: HUP!
HELLO, MY YOUNG ACTORS.

12:31.375 --> 12:33.043
ALL BUT BLAINE:
HELLO, SIR COACH.

12:33.127 --> 12:34.003
BLAINE: ROAR!

12:34.086 --> 12:36.338
{\an1}NELLA:
WOW. WHAT'S THAT, SIR COACH?

12:36.422 --> 12:38.716
THIS, PRINCESS NELLA, IS
THE STAGE FOR OUR PLAY.

12:38.799 --> 12:41.844
YOU SEE, WE'RE
A TRAVELING THEATER,

12:41.927 --> 12:43.345
AND OUR STAGE IS
ON WHEELS

12:43.429 --> 12:45.473
SO WE CAN PERFORM
ALL OVER THE KINGDOM.

12:45.556 --> 12:46.640
{\an1}COOL!

12:45.556 --> 12:46.640
COOL!

12:46.724 --> 12:49.101
NOW, AS YOU KNOW, TODAY
WE'RE GOING TO PUT ON

12:49.185 --> 12:50.102
"THE BRAVE DRAGON,"

12:50.186 --> 12:53.230
AND THE STORY HAS A LOT
OF GREAT PARTS.

12:53.314 --> 12:54.190
BLAINE: BUT ONLY ONE OF THEM
IS THE BEST,

12:54.273 --> 12:57.693
JUST LIKE ONLY ONE
OF US IS THE BEST--

12:57.776 --> 12:58.319
ME--THE BLAINESTER.

12:58.402 --> 13:00.404
LET'S SEE HERE.

13:00.488 --> 13:03.407
FIRST WE NEED TWO
WOODLAND CRITTERS.

13:03.491 --> 13:05.868
HEY, HOW ABOUT YOU,
NELLA AND TRINKET?

13:05.951 --> 13:08.537
UM, WELL, OK.

13:09.663 --> 13:13.042
{\an1}I'LL PLAY ANYTHING WITH
A CUTE, FLUFFY TAIL.

13:13.125 --> 13:14.668
AND, CLOD...

13:14.752 --> 13:15.669
{\an1}YEAH?

13:15.753 --> 13:17.796
SIR COACH: YOU CAN BE
THE EVIL WIZARD.

13:17.880 --> 13:19.006
{\an1}[GASPS]

13:19.089 --> 13:21.217
{\an1}AWESOME!

13:21.300 --> 13:25.888
I AM THE EVIL WIZARD.
ZAP! ZAP! ZAP! ZAP...

13:25.971 --> 13:27.473
[KIDS AND TRINKET LAUGHING]

13:27.556 --> 13:28.557
SIR COACH: AND NOW
FOR THE LEAD ROLE

13:28.641 --> 13:32.228
OF THE BRAVE
DRAGON.

13:32.311 --> 13:35.105
I CHOOSE...
GARRETT.

13:35.189 --> 13:36.482
THANK YOU, SIR COACH.

13:36.565 --> 13:38.484
I KNOW THAT WASN'T
A DIFFICULT DECISION,

13:38.567 --> 13:41.570
BUT--WAIT! DID YOU SAY
"GARRETT"?

13:41.654 --> 13:43.822
{\an1}REALLY? I GET TO BE
THE BRAVE DRAGON?

13:43.906 --> 13:46.408
YUP. I THINK YOU'LL
BE TERRIFIC.

13:46.492 --> 13:48.994
{\an1}WAY TO GO,
BUDDY!

13:49.078 --> 13:50.204
NELLA:
WOW, GARRETT!

13:50.287 --> 13:51.497
AND WHAT PART
DO I GET?

13:51.580 --> 13:55.084
WELL, BLAINE, THERE'S JUST
ONE VERY SPECIAL PART LEFT,

13:55.167 --> 13:56.919
A ROLE I REALLY
THINK YOU'LL LIKE--

13:57.002 --> 13:59.213
THE BUMBLE-BUG.

13:59.296 --> 14:02.216
THE BUMBLE-BUG?

14:02.299 --> 14:04.385
{\an1}YOU WANT ME
TO PLAY THE BUMBLE-BUG?

14:04.468 --> 14:06.887
TRUST ME. YOU'LL BE
GREAT AT IT.

14:06.971 --> 14:07.972
UGH.

14:08.055 --> 14:09.598
IS EVERYTHING OK,
SIR BLAINE?

14:09.682 --> 14:12.685
{\an1}NO. EVERYTHING
IS TERRIBLE, NELLA.

14:12.768 --> 14:14.228
{\an1}I HAVE TO PLAY THE PART
OF THE BUMBLE-BUG,

14:14.311 --> 14:18.941
{\an1}BUT I REALLY WANTED TO PLAY
THE PART OF THE BRAVE DRAGON.

14:19.024 --> 14:20.234
YEAH, I KNOW.

14:20.317 --> 14:22.278
I WANTED TO BE
THE BRAVE DRAGON, TOO.

14:22.361 --> 14:23.862
GUESS WE'LL JUST HAVE
TO MAKE THE MOST

14:23.946 --> 14:24.613
OF WHAT WE'VE GOT.

14:24.697 --> 14:27.116
SIR COACH: COME ON, ACTORS.

14:27.199 --> 14:28.242
{\an1}LET'S GET THIS SHOW
ON THE ROAD.

14:28.325 --> 14:30.578
{\an1}[EXHALES]

14:30.661 --> 14:33.122
{\an1}I DON'T WANT TO EVEN
BE IN THIS PLAY ANYMORE.

14:33.205 --> 14:33.831
{\an1}[CHIRPS]

14:33.914 --> 14:36.166
SIR COACH:
HERE WE ARE.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.335
HERE'S THE SPOT
FOR THE SHOW.

14:38.419 --> 14:40.796
I THINK WE'RE READY
TO--WHOA! OOPS!

14:40.879 --> 14:43.465
HEH. I DIDN'T PUT
THE BRAKE ON.

14:43.549 --> 14:47.011
HA HA HA. JUST ONE
MORE THING. THERE.

14:50.556 --> 14:51.557
THERE.

14:51.640 --> 14:54.310
{\an5}WOW!

14:51.640 --> 14:54.310
WOW!

14:51.640 --> 14:54.310
{\an3}WOW!

14:54.393 --> 14:56.186
NOW WE'RE READY
TO START.

14:56.270 --> 15:00.983
OOH, LOOK, PEOPLE
ARE COMING OVER

15:01.066 --> 15:02.484
TO SEE OUR PLAY.

15:02.568 --> 15:05.863
{\an1}TRINKET: OH, AND CAN I SAY,
WE ALL LOOK DAZZLING

15:05.946 --> 15:07.489
IN OUR COSTUMES.

15:07.573 --> 15:10.284
BLAINE: I REALLY DON'T WANT
TO BE IN THIS PLAY ANYMORE.

15:10.367 --> 15:11.493
SIR COACH: AH,
DON'T WORRY, BLAINE.

15:11.577 --> 15:14.038
THE SHOW WILL BE GREAT.

15:14.121 --> 15:15.998
JUST HAVE FUN
OUT THERE, KIDS.

15:16.081 --> 15:17.916
AND, REMEMBER,
WHATEVER HAPPENS,

15:18.000 --> 15:19.501
KEEP ON ACTING.

15:19.585 --> 15:22.087
GARRETT, TRINKET, CLOD,
AND NELLA: THE SHOW MUST GO ON!

15:22.171 --> 15:23.464
[LAUGHTER]

15:25.841 --> 15:28.135
AHEM! HELLO, NOBLES
AND GENTLE KNIGHTS,

15:28.218 --> 15:33.432
AND WELCOME TO OUR PERFORMANCE
OF "THE BRAVE DRAGON,"

15:33.515 --> 15:37.061
{\an1}WHICH BEGINS WITHOUT
FURTHER ADO.

15:38.520 --> 15:42.399
{\an1}NELLA: CHITTER, CHITTER.
HERE WE ARE.

15:42.483 --> 15:44.193
SQUEAK, SQUEAK.

15:44.276 --> 15:45.569
IN THE WOODS.

15:45.653 --> 15:47.988
{\an1}TWO ADORABLE
WOODLAND CRITTERS.

15:50.324 --> 15:51.700
{\an1}ALL RIGHT, BLAINE,
IT'S ALMOST TIME

15:51.784 --> 15:54.828
{\an1}FOR THE BUMBLE-BUG
TO FLY IN.

15:54.912 --> 15:56.205
WHATEVER.

15:56.288 --> 15:58.374
{\an1}NELLA:
CHITTER, CHITTER. OK.

15:58.457 --> 16:00.918
{\an1}HERE COMES
THE BUMBLE-BUG.

16:02.795 --> 16:07.716
{\an1}I SAID, HERE COMES
THE BUMBLE-BUG.

16:07.800 --> 16:09.551
THAT'S YOUR CUE, BLAINE.

16:09.635 --> 16:13.097
REMEMBER TO HOLD
THE ROPE.

16:13.180 --> 16:14.473
YEAH, YEAH.

16:14.556 --> 16:18.060
OK. HERE HE GOES.

16:18.143 --> 16:19.895
WHOA!

16:18.143 --> 16:19.895
HOLD THE ROPE.

16:19.978 --> 16:21.980
BLAINE: WHOA!

16:22.064 --> 16:23.190
{\an1}OHH.

16:22.064 --> 16:23.190
HA HA!

16:23.273 --> 16:26.652
LOOK, IT'S
THE BUMBLE-BUG...

16:26.735 --> 16:27.903
{\an1}WAAH!

16:27.986 --> 16:29.613
FLYING UPSIDE-DOWN.

16:29.697 --> 16:31.240
AAH!

16:31.323 --> 16:33.325
OOF. GOTCHA.

16:33.409 --> 16:35.619
PHEW!

16:35.703 --> 16:38.664
{\an1}SO WHAT DID YOU FLY IN
TO TELL US,

16:38.747 --> 16:41.166
MR. BUMBLE-BUG, SIR?

16:42.501 --> 16:44.753
[COUGHS]

16:44.837 --> 16:45.754
COME ON, BLAINE.
KEEP ON ACTING.

16:45.838 --> 16:50.134
OH, UH, I CAME
TO SAY THERE'S

16:50.217 --> 16:52.219
AN EVIL WIZARD
IN THE WOODS.

16:52.302 --> 16:54.972
AN EVIL WIZARD?

16:55.055 --> 16:56.223
[DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING]

16:56.306 --> 16:57.808
TRINKET AND NELLA: OH!

16:57.891 --> 17:02.104
YES, I AM
AN EVIL WIZARD.

17:02.187 --> 17:03.439
ZAP, ZAP, ZAP.

17:03.522 --> 17:04.606
GREAT SCENE, BLAINE.

17:04.690 --> 17:07.443
I MEAN, IT WASN'T WHAT
WE WERE SUPPOSED TO DO,

17:07.526 --> 17:09.611
{\an1}BUT THE AUDIENCE THOUGHT
IT WAS REALLY FUNNY.

17:09.694 --> 17:13.741
OK. IT'S ALMOST TIME
FOR MY BIG ENTRANCE.

17:13.824 --> 17:17.118
{\an1}GO GET 'EM, GARRETT.
YOU'LL DO GREAT.

17:17.202 --> 17:20.289
HMPH. IF GARRETT'S PART
WERE MINE, I WOULD DO

17:20.372 --> 17:21.665
EVEN GREATER.

17:21.749 --> 17:26.295
SO WHY DON'T I JUST TAKE
GARRETT'S PART

17:26.377 --> 17:28.213
FOR MYSELF?

17:28.297 --> 17:29.631
HMM, HMM, HMM!

17:29.715 --> 17:34.011
I'LL JUST TIE HIS TAIL
TO THIS POLE.

17:35.262 --> 17:36.805
AND I AM HERE...

17:36.889 --> 17:38.599
{\an1}SIR COACH:
OK, GARRETT, YOU'RE ON.

17:38.682 --> 17:39.725
{\an1}CLOD AS WIZARD: ...TO CAPTURE
THE WOODLAND CRITTERS...

17:39.808 --> 17:40.684
{\an1}STOP,
EVIL WIZAR--WHOA!

17:40.768 --> 17:44.897
HA HA! AND THE PART IS MINE.

17:44.980 --> 17:47.316
STOP EVIL WIZARD.

17:47.399 --> 17:49.234
WELL, WELL, WELL.

17:49.318 --> 17:51.278
WE MEET AT LAST,
BRAVE...

17:51.361 --> 17:52.154
BUMBLE-BUG?

17:52.237 --> 17:55.824
NO, NO, NO. I AM
THE BRAVE DRAGON.

17:55.908 --> 18:01.163
HMM, YOU LOOK LIKE
THE BUMBLE-BUG.

18:01.246 --> 18:02.206
BLAINE: WELL, I'M NOT.

18:02.289 --> 18:05.417
{\an1}AND I WILL PROVE IT TO YOU
BY DEFEATING YOU

18:05.501 --> 18:06.835
WITH MY WOODEN STINGER--

18:06.919 --> 18:11.215
{\an1}I MEAN, UH,
MY WOODEN SWORD. HA HA!

18:11.298 --> 18:12.591
TAKE ONE OF THESE.

18:12.674 --> 18:14.009
{\an1}SIR COACH: WELL,
THIS ISN'T IN THE SCRIPT.

18:14.092 --> 18:18.514
HUP. AND ONE OF--
UH-OH. I'M STUCK.

18:18.597 --> 18:20.057
[AUDIENCE LAUGHING]

18:20.140 --> 18:21.308
NO. SERIOUSLY.

18:21.391 --> 18:22.810
{\an1}[GROANS]

18:22.893 --> 18:26.063
{\an1}MY STINGER'S STUCK.
I CAN'T GET OUT.

18:26.146 --> 18:27.856
[GRUNTS]

18:27.940 --> 18:30.192
WHOA!

18:30.275 --> 18:31.235
OOPS.

18:33.570 --> 18:36.532
{\an1}OH, MY GOSH! THE STAGE
IS ROLLING AWAY.

18:36.615 --> 18:37.199
CLOD AND GARRETT: WHOA!

18:37.282 --> 18:38.992
I'VE GOT TO STOP IT.

18:39.076 --> 18:40.494
MY HEART IS BRIGHT,

18:40.577 --> 18:42.538
TIME TO BE
A PRINCESS KNIGHT.

18:42.621 --> 18:44.456
♪ MY HEART GROWS STRONG ♪

18:44.540 --> 18:45.207
♪ IT'S TIME TO
SHINE MY LIGHT ♪

18:45.290 --> 18:48.043
♪ SWORD, SHIELD, BOOTS ♪

18:48.126 --> 18:50.170
♪ MY COURAGE SHININ'
BRIGHT ♪

18:50.254 --> 18:52.381
♪ NOW I AM ♪

18:52.464 --> 18:54.591
♪ THE PRINCESS KNIGHT ♪

18:54.675 --> 18:56.468
TALK ABOUT A SHOWSTOPPER.

18:56.552 --> 18:59.972
{\an1}COME ON, TRINK.
AFTER THAT STAGE.

19:00.055 --> 19:03.350
BLAINE, GARRETT, AND CLOD:
WHOA!

19:03.433 --> 19:04.893
{\an1}OOH!

19:03.433 --> 19:04.893
OOH!

19:04.977 --> 19:06.562
HOLD ON, KIDS!

19:06.645 --> 19:08.564
DON'T WORRY.
WE'RE COMING, GUYS.

19:08.647 --> 19:09.648
CAN YOU PICK UP
THE SPEED, TRINK?

19:09.731 --> 19:11.066
OF COURSE, NELLA.

19:11.149 --> 19:15.487
{\an1}TIME TO PUT MY CUTE
FUZZY TAIL INTO ACTION!

19:15.571 --> 19:18.490
NELLA: WHOO-HOO!
WE'RE ALMOST...

19:18.574 --> 19:20.284
THERE.

19:20.367 --> 19:22.536
ANYBODY HOME?

19:22.619 --> 19:24.037
BLAINE: AMAZING!

19:22.619 --> 19:24.037
INCREDIBLE!

19:24.121 --> 19:25.581
GARRETT: GAUNTLETS. IT'S
GOOD TO SEE YOU, NELLA.

19:25.664 --> 19:26.999
[CHUCKLES]

19:27.082 --> 19:29.668
THANKS, GUYS, BUT WE
CAN'T CELEBRATE YET.

19:29.751 --> 19:31.712
{\an1}WE STILL NEED TO FIND
A WAY TO STOP.

19:31.795 --> 19:34.423
{\an1}EASY. I'LL JUST PULL
ON THE BRAKE.

19:34.506 --> 19:36.466
[CLOD GASPS]

19:36.550 --> 19:38.343
OH, NO!
THE BRAKE BROKE.

19:38.427 --> 19:40.095
WELL, THERE GOES STOPPING.

19:40.178 --> 19:42.055
KIDS AND CLOD: WHOA!

19:42.139 --> 19:44.766
UH-OH. WE GOT TO STEER
THIS STAGE,

19:44.850 --> 19:47.269
{\an1}AND I KNOW JUST HOW
TO DO IT.

19:51.064 --> 19:53.233
{\an1}THESE RIBBONS WILL HELP ME
TURN THE WHEELS.

19:56.445 --> 19:58.238
CLOD: GO, NELLA!

19:58.322 --> 19:59.531
NELLA: WHOO-HOO!

19:59.615 --> 20:01.199
SIR COACH: MY GOODNESS, NELLA!

20:01.283 --> 20:02.993
WAY TO GO!

20:03.076 --> 20:05.746
NELLA: OH! UGH!

20:09.875 --> 20:11.793
TRINKET: WE STOPPED.

20:11.877 --> 20:13.128
YAY, NELLA, YOU DID IT!

20:13.211 --> 20:15.797
{\an1}BLAINE: BUT OUR SHOW
IS STILL RUINED.

20:15.881 --> 20:18.300
THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.

20:18.383 --> 20:21.386
{\an1}I KNEW I SHOULDN'T HAVE
BEEN IN THIS PLAY.

20:21.470 --> 20:22.971
I'M THE WORST ACTOR EVER.

20:23.055 --> 20:26.475
BLAINE, THAT'S NOT TRUE.

20:26.558 --> 20:27.643
YES, IT IS.

20:27.726 --> 20:29.353
I WAS TERRIBLE, NELLA.

20:29.436 --> 20:30.938
{\an1}THE AUDIENCE JUST
LAUGHED AT ME.

20:31.021 --> 20:33.482
GARRETT: YEAH, 'CAUSE
YOU WERE FUNNY.

20:33.565 --> 20:35.734
REALLY? I--I WAS?

20:35.817 --> 20:36.568
TRINKET, CLOD, AND SIR COACH:
YEAH!

20:36.652 --> 20:38.236
BLAINE, I KNOW YOU
WANTED TO BE

20:38.320 --> 20:39.363
THE BRAVE DRAGON,

20:39.446 --> 20:41.281
BUT YOU COULD'VE
MADE A GREAT BUMBLE-BUG.

20:41.365 --> 20:43.533
{\an1}I SHOULD'VE MADE
THE MOST OF WHAT I HAD.

20:43.617 --> 20:45.744
{\an1}EXACTLY!

20:45.827 --> 20:47.829
[WOOD CREAKING]

20:49.790 --> 20:51.833
{\an1}NELLA: OH, NO.
WE'RE ROLLING AGAIN

20:51.917 --> 20:52.834
BACK DOWN THE HILL!

20:52.918 --> 20:55.170
BLAINE: WHOA! WHOA!

20:55.253 --> 20:58.382
MAN: HEY, LOOK,
THERE'S THE STAGE.

20:58.465 --> 21:00.092
{\an1}WHOA!

20:58.465 --> 21:00.092
WHOA!

21:00.175 --> 21:03.136
BLAINE: WE'VE GOT TO SLOW DOWN,
NELLA, BUT HOW?

21:03.220 --> 21:05.389
UM...

21:05.472 --> 21:09.101
{\an1}I'VE GOT IT, BUT I'M GONNA
NEED YOUR HELP, BLAINE,

21:09.184 --> 21:10.686
AND YOUR STINGER.

21:10.769 --> 21:12.270
NO PROBLEM.

21:12.354 --> 21:15.190
I'M GONNA MAKE THE MOST
OF WHAT I'VE GOT.

21:15.273 --> 21:17.192
[GRUNTING]

21:20.278 --> 21:20.946
[CHUCKLING]

21:21.029 --> 21:23.281
{\an1}ALL RIGHT!

21:21.029 --> 21:23.281
WHOO-HOO!

21:23.365 --> 21:23.865
YEAH!

21:23.365 --> 21:23.865
TRINKET: PERFECT!

21:23.949 --> 21:25.409
BLAINE: UH-OH.

21:30.831 --> 21:32.374
BLAINE: YEAH! WE DID IT!

21:32.457 --> 21:33.625
WHOO-HOO!

21:33.709 --> 21:36.128
{\an1}AMAZING WORK, KIDS,
BUT QUICK.

21:36.211 --> 21:38.547
{\an1}WE STILL NEED
TO FINISH THE PLAY.

21:38.630 --> 21:41.091
PLACES, EVERYONE. PLACES.

21:41.174 --> 21:43.969
{\an1}AND SO, THANKS
TO THE BRAVE DRAGON,

21:44.052 --> 21:46.972
{\an1}THE EVIL WIZARD
WAS DEFEATED,

21:47.055 --> 21:49.766
AND ALL THE WOODLAND
CRITTERS WERE SAFE.

21:49.850 --> 21:54.730
{\an1}BLAINE: INCLUDING
THE BUMBLE-BUG. WHOA!

21:54.813 --> 21:57.232
ALL: THE END.

21:57.315 --> 22:00.318
[CHEERING]

22:00.402 --> 22:02.362
SIR COACH: WHAT A SHOW.
